  {
    "client_msg_id": "be482ac0-da41-4b1a-a7b9-971c84793c18",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "I take the opposite view to <@UCUSW7WVD> — communities make or break a programming language. I might even tentatively propose that historically, language design has been secondary to social/cultural/community factors when it comes to success or failure (otherwise how could something like c++ or JS be so popular :wink:?) Though I think for end-users (and groups thereof) design matters a lot more than for developer-targeted languages, since clarity is paramount.",
    "user": "U6FKVSVCK",
    "ts": "1566240280.158200",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
